{
  "texts": [
    "Restrictions are mandated on targeting minors or using sensitive data for targeting without explicit consent.",
    "Independent audits must confirm platforms' ad repositories cover qualifying ads comprehensively and accurately.Risk assessment obligations ( Articles 26,34,35) VLOPs are subjected to extensive risk assessment requirements to identify and mitigate societal dangers emerging from the misuse or shortcomings of their content moderation systems, algorithmic processes, business models and behavioral designs.Articles 26, 27, 34 and related recitals impose extensive systemic risk assessment and mitigation requirements on VLOPs to address societal dangers emerging from their services.",
    "Ps must conduct annual risk assessments evaluating how their content moderation systems, algorithmic processes, business models, and interface designs negatively impact: (i) User security and fundamental rights like non-discrimination, freedom of expression, media freedom (Article 26; Recital 82); (ii) Democratic discourse, electoral processes, public security (Article 26; Recital 82); (iii) Equality issues like gender-based violence or threats to minors (Article 26; Recital 83).",
    "Risks must be assessed from illegal content distribution, inauthentic platform use, and lawful but harmful content.",
    "Risks from data practices, biased algorithms, and exploitative interface designs should also be evaluated (Articles 27, 34; Recital 84).Once risks are identified, VLOPs must implement reasonable, targeted and proportionate measures to mitigate them within mandated timeframes (Article 35)."
  ]
}